The paper deals with the development of a learning-based adaptive observer for a class of second-order nonlinear time-invariant systems with uncertain dynamics. This involves the estimation of both the state and parameters of the system. The paper is likely to belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) category, as it deals with the development of an observer for a class of nonlinear systems. Additionally, the use of learning-based techniques suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) categories. The use of adaptive control techniques suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) category. Finally, the use of simulation results suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the Robotics (cs.RO) category.
